    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Arredondo, Florida</name>
                    <date when="1878-02-21">February 21, 1878</date>
                </dateline><!-- is this information in the actual letter?-nnk -->
                <salute>Dear Friend,</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I receive a postal from you this date address to me at New Britain <choice>
                <orig>Conn.</orig><reg>Connecticut</reg></choice><ptr target="n0514"/> I am well
                and so is my Family. My health is better than it has been in some time <space unit="chars" quantity="3"/> I have a
                little place here and are <choice>
                    <sic>triing</sic>
                    <corr>trying</corr>
                </choice> hard to get along. I am raising <choice>
                    <sic>vedgeables</sic>
                    <corr>vegetables</corr>
                </choice> for the New York market <space unit="chars" quantity="3"/> it is the busy season here now <space unit="chars" quantity="3"/> I was glad to hear
                from you and that you are better <space unit="chars" quantity="3"/> I have thought of you a good many times <space unit="chars" quantity="3"/> I should
                like to see you and if God <choice>
                    <sic>spairs</sic>
                    <corr>spares</corr>
                </choice> our lives I hope to see you once more but God know what is best, if we but
                look to him he will take care of us and make our griefs and pains easy to bear <space unit="chars" quantity="3"/> I
                have often thought of what you have had to go through and suffer in your sickness. I
                wish that you <choice>
                    <sic>whare</sic>
                    <corr>were</corr>
                </choice> that I could see you and comfort you. I have got a <choice>
                    <orig>find</orig>
                    <reg>fine</reg>
                </choice> little boy <space unit="chars" quantity="3"/> I have named him after you he is now <choice>
                    <orig>most</orig>
                    <reg>almost</reg>
                </choice> four years old will be in June next. I should be happy to hear from you as
                soon as you get this</p>

            <closer>
                <salute>write soon, From your <choice>
                        <sic>affecinate</sic>
                        <corr>affectionate</corr>
                    </choice> Friend and well wisher,</salute>
                <signed>John M. Rogers.</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
